We all know, said the oil ministry spokesman, Assam Jihad, that China is on its way to become one of the biggest in the world economy as well as a technology power.
We are convinced that the Chinese company will be able to measure itself with its co-offerers and will fulfill its commitments to Iraq.
Pre-selected companies issued bids for bidding, which were then compared to the fee per barrel of oil that the ministry was willing to pay in order to increase the emissions of each field beyond the current level.
